  "text": "In this section, we develop a pairwise key establishment scheme named closest pairwise keys scheme to take advantage of the expected location information. The basic idea is to have each sensor node share pairwise keys with a number of other sensor nodes whose expected locations are closest to the expected location of this sensor node. The following discussion starts with a basic version, which can be considered as the combination of the random pairwise keys scheme [CITATION_1] ] and the expected location information, and then gives an extended version to further reduce the storage overhead and facilitate dynamic deployment of new sensor nodes.",
